body:
As per the original implementation [1] of the absolute and relative page flipping mechanism:
- The sequence/reserved field should not hold these `DRM_MODE_PAGE_FLIP_TARGET_*` flags but the sequence number;
- The flag is instead passed through the `flags` member;
- Either `ABSOLUTE` or `RELATIVE` is supposed to be passed, not both (which is `DRM_MODE_PAGE_FLIP_TARGET`, and would always result in `-EINVAL`);

[1]: https://git.kernel.org/torvalds/c/f837297ad82480024d3ad08cd84f6670bcafa862
